## üîê Security Best Practices

### 1. Use Environment Variables
```powershell
# Never hardcode credentials in code!
$env:API_KEY="your_secret_key"
```

### 2. Use Windows Credential Manager
```powershell
# Store credentials securely
cmdkey /add:CHIMERA_AWS /user:aws /pass:your_password

# Retrieve
cmdkey /list | findstr CHIMERA
```

### 3. Enable SSL
```powershell
# Generate self-signed certificate
New-SelfSignedCertificate -DnsName "localhost" -CertStoreLocation "cert:\LocalMachine\My"

# Export to PEM (use OpenSSL or certutil)
```

## üöÄ Performance Tips

### 1. Use SSD for Models
Store trained LSTM models on SSD for faster loading:
```powershell
# Move models to SSD
Move-Item -Path ".\models" -Destination "D:\fast_storage\chimera_models"
New-Item -ItemType SymbolicLink -Path ".\models" -Target "D:\fast_storage\chimera_models"
```

### 2. Increase Python Priority
```powershell
# Run CHIMERA with high priority
Start-Process -FilePath "python" -ArgumentList "chimera_autarch.py" -Priority High
```

### 3. Disable Windows Defender Real-Time Scanning (for Python folder)
Add exclusion in Windows Security ‚Üí Virus & threat protection ‚Üí Exclusions

### 4. Use Windows Terminal
Install from Microsoft Store for better performance and features:
```powershell
winget install Microsoft.WindowsTerminal
```

